Scenario: 1
Part 1: Effective promotions and channel strategies
Q 1.1: What priority of channels will you recommend for future promotion?
As it can be seen in the table from previous slide, the profit margin for promotions via:
● Website display is 87.77
● TV ads is 86.934
● Print ads is 86.697
● Social media is 85.219
● Events is 74.02.
Here the profit margin for website display is coming out to be the highest which is 87.77, and lowest for Events.
This calculation has been done for X = 97, where 1X is the spending done on one social media impression. This
value was calculated as,
($1.03 million)X = $100 million
where, $100 million is our promotional budget and ($1.03million)X is the sum of the cost of all the channels.
So the priority order would be:
Website display > TV ads > Print ads > Social media > Events.

Q 1.2: As per the market research conducted by Pulse Beverages to
understand the channel accessibility and popularity:
(a) Which 3 channel would you pick considering outcomes from
both Q1.1 and Q1.2?
According to both access rating and popularity ratings, social
media tops the charts. Though website is easily accessible, it is
not popular. Both TV ads and Print ads are equally accessible and
popular. And events are neither accessible nor popular. So looking
at both profit margin ad ratings, the three channels that we would
pick are:
● Social Media
● TV ads
● Print ads

Part 2: Assessing TV campaign and customer preferences
Q 2.3:Pulse has also planned to launch a new product (Aqualite) along with the current drink. Based on
your current understanding and analysis, what promotional strategies would you recommend for the new
product in terms of (also consider impact of COVID on customer preferences):
Type of product, Channels for promotion, Segment of customers, and Content & messaging
● Type of Product: It can be a healthier alternative to Aqua with lesser carbs, for people who are
more health conscious and want to check their calories.
● Channels for Promotion: The same channels like social media, TV ads, Print ads and Website
display will be helpful in the promotion of the product.
● Segment of Customers: We think mostly our target customers would be young corporates and mid
to senior citizens as they are working and have a very hectic schedule. So we think that they would
want to be fit so as to cope up with daily activities.
● Content and messaging: As already mentioned, it can have the same ingredients and health
supplements as aqua but with lesser carbs. It can be branded as an healthier alternative.

Scenario: 1
Part 3: Allocating the promotional budget optimally
Q 3.1: What should be the optimal promotional spend on the various channels? Out of the 5 channels
listed, Pulse wants to spend the promotion budget on 3 channels only, so the optimal spend should be
calculated for 3 out of the 5 channels.
After calculating the ROI for all the channels for different number of ads and impressions (all the
calculations given in slide 15), we have come up with the following optimum spend for different
channels. Instead of going for the highest ROI for a particular channel, we went for the option which
would generate the maximum revenue, all this while staying within the limit of the promotional budget.
As we can see from the table, websites have the smallest investment and highest sales, thus
generating a huge revenue and highest ROI. So the three channels out 5 that we choose are,
➔ 1) Website display, 2) TV ads and 3) Print ads.
And the optimum promotional spend is $15.055 million

Q 3.3: Given the budget allocation in previous question and based on additional data in slide 12, should
the company change its strategy of not using a certain channel to target a specific segment?
As it can be seen from the table the most time spent for various segments is
● Children - TV
● Young corporates - Social Network and Browsing Internet
● Mid to senior citizens - TV
● Senior citizens - Print
So it is quite conclusive that the optimum choices of channels, i.e., website display, TV ads and print ads, that
we have made is very versatile and caters to all the age segments. So even if we stick to the previous strategy
of using only 3 out of 5 channels, we are able to reach everyone. But if we also go with social media, then with
quite a small investment we can generate a revenue of extra $35 million. Events don’t have that much of a
preference in any of the segments and have a low ROI. So we can go for 4 channels, leaving out events.
